1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:54,550
He won!

3
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:59,000
Arlong Park has fallen!

4
00:02:01,130 --> 00:02:02,760
We did it, older sister!

5
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:02,760
Gen!

6
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:06,600
This... This isn't a dream, right?

7
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,690
I never thought this day would come.

8
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:25,330
Way to go, Luffy! I'll throw in my compliments, too!

9
00:02:25,330 --> 00:02:27,360
Though, I'd praise you even more,

10
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:31,170
if you would've given me more of a starring role!

11
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:34,170
Man, talk about being on pins and needles.

12
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:39,630
Next time, wrap it up a bit quicker, you damn jerk!

13
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:10,210
This is awesome!

14
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,220
All right, that's enough of that!

15
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:27,220
It's that guy...!

16
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:30,930
What a lucky day today is!

17
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:34,670
Well done.
I watched the entire fight.

18
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:39,740
Fluke or not, I never once imagined the fishmen would lose

19
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:42,200
to a band of no-name pirates like you.

20
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:46,630
However, thanks to you,
all the money I was to give Arlong

21
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:50,970
and anything of value found in Arlong Park is now mine!

22
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:52,370
Everyone drop your weapons!

23
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:58,130
The credit for this incident now belongs
to me, Captain Nezumi of the Navy 16th Branch!

24
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,710
Zoro!

25
00:04:01,110 --> 00:04:04,970
Don't rain on people's parade while they're rejoicing!

26
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:16,210
J-Just you try to lay a finger on me! You'll be sorry!

27
00:04:16,210 --> 00:04:17,770
Are you still talking?

28
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,120
This is for shooting Nojiko...

29
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:28,640
and for tearing up Bell-mère's tangerine orchard.

30
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,330
Huh?

31
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:33,410
Captain!

32
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:40,630
Thanks, Nami! That felt good!

33
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:43,300
Give 'im 1,000 more of those!

34
00:04:49,410 --> 00:04:52,670
You marines are gonna clean up
after these fishmen now!

35
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:55,190
And you're gonna help rebuild the town of Gosa!

36
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:59,400
And you're not gonna touch
anything of value in Arlong Park!

37
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,530
That's the island's money! Got it?!

38
00:05:01,530 --> 00:05:05,570
Ow! Ow! I-I'll do what you say!

39
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:07,160
And one other thing!

40
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:09,410
Give me my money back!

41
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:14,870
I'll give it back! I'll give it back!
It's not worth it anymore!

42
00:05:18,070 --> 00:05:20,570
I'll get you, you rotten pirates!

43
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:23,300
Straw hat man!
Your name's Luffy, right?!

44
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:26,430
You're the captain, right?!
Remember this!

45
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:29,260
You're in for quite the ride!
You've pushed me too far!

46
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:31,490
It's too late for regrets!

47
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:35,330
I will have my revenge!
Just you wait and see!

48
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:37,860
He says we're in for quite the ride.

49
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:41,190
How does he know I'm gonna be king of the pirates?

50
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:44,090
That's not what he means!
Man, you're stupid!

51
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:47,690
H-Hey, what do we do?! What if we really do wind up in big trouble?!

52
00:05:47,690 --> 00:05:49,780
Hey! Hey! What'll we do?!

53
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:54,090
Alright, everyone!
We can't have all the fun!

54
00:05:54,090 --> 00:05:57,890
Everyone on the island needs to know about this monumental event!

55
00:05:59,790 --> 00:06:01,190
Arlong Park...

56
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:04,010
Arlong Park has fallen!

57
00:06:24,330 --> 00:06:26,530
Good for you, Nami!

58
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:31,810
I can't believe we were saved by pirates.

59
00:06:31,810 --> 00:06:33,790
Life's full of surprises.

60
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,510
Headquarters?! Navy Headquarters?!

61
00:06:36,510 --> 00:06:41,050
Hello! This is Captain Nezumi of the 16th Branch!

62
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:43,790
Marine code 00733!

63
00:06:44,150 --> 00:06:45,610
I have a request for HQ!

64
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:52,300
Listen! There's a pirate named Luffy,
who wears a straw hat!

65
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:47,970
You don't need to shout.
I can hear you.

66
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:56,770
I deem him and his four crew members enemies of the government!

67
00:06:57,190 --> 00:07:01,730
I deem him and his four crew members enemies of the government!

68
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:03,360
"Luffy."

69
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,620
They managed to take down
the purportedly invincible Arlong Pirates,

70
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,670
the fishmen of Arlong Park!

71
00:07:08,670 --> 00:07:14,870
Considering this threat, I have placed
a hefty bounty on the captain, Straw Hat Luffy!

72
00:07:14,870 --> 00:07:16,390
I'm now sending a photograph!

73
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:17,620
Roger that.

74
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,330
Huh?!

75
00:07:22,330 --> 00:07:25,030
Couldn't you have taken a better one?!

76
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:26,800
No, that's all I could get.

77
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:31,800
After a quick verification,
I will submit it for approval.

78
00:07:32,570 --> 00:07:36,470
Don't forget, now!
He's a vile pirate! "Dead or Alive"!

79
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:42,050
Put him on wanted posters across the globe!

80
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,610
He's still at it.

81
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:53,320
Sounds like ol' Zoro's really hurtin'.

82
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,940
Well, yeah.

83
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:57,870
An average person with those wounds would take two years to fully heal!

84
00:07:59,470 --> 00:08:00,950
You moron!

85
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:03,870
Trying to take care of such a grave injury on your own!

86
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:04,990
Oww!

87
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:08,180
Honestly! Are you folks really pirates?!

88
00:08:08,180 --> 00:08:11,430
Do you even have...
a ship's doctor?!

89
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:13,880
A doctor? That sounds good, too!

90
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:14,780
Luffy?

91
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:16,990
But a musician comes first.
Right, Zoro?

92
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:18,270
Why's that?!

93
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:20,650
Because pirates sing, you know!

94
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:23,310
So why does that come first?!

95
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:26,700
Hey, Doctor. Where's Nami?

96
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:29,180
She doesn't seem to be here, either.

97
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,670
Nami, huh?

98
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:34,370
If you can't find her around,
then she's probably where she always goes.

99
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:49,710
What?! You're still here, Nami?

100
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:52,710
Your friends've been looking for you, you know.

101
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:59,050
Hey, Nojiko... Gen.

102
00:08:59,050 --> 00:09:01,570
If Bell-mère were alive,

103
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:05,160
do you think she'd stop me from being a pirate?

104
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,080
A pirate?!

105
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,020
Give me a break!

106
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:12,090
There's no way she'd ever let
her precious daughter be a pirate!

107
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:13,140
She wouldn't stop you!

108
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:13,900
Nojiko!

109
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,030
Even if she tried,

110
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:17,490
would you really listen to her?

111
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:21,540
Absolutely not!

112
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,720
Whew, I'm stuffed!

113
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:37,980
Sometimes it's nice to just eat!

114
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,000
Are your wounds all better now, Zoro?

115
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,840
This's nothin'! Some food and drink'll fix it right up!

116
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,320
Yeah?

117
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:47,230
But how long is this dumb party gonna last?

118
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,620
This is the third day now!

119
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,230
What's wrong with that?

120
00:09:51,230 --> 00:09:54,740
When you wanna celebrate,
you should pull out all the stops.

121
00:09:55,490 --> 00:09:58,470
Hey, Sanji!
That melon you just had!

122
00:09:58,470 --> 00:10:00,140
Was there something on it?!

123
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:02,290
What's with all that meat?!

124
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:05,940
Sure was. It's prosciutto and melon, so there was prosciutto on it.

125
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:08,960
Prosciutto and melon?! That sounds great! Wh-Where did you get it?!

126
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,420
Dunno.

127
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:14,760
The whole village is a buffet party,
so I dunno where I got it.

128
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,750
He's long gone.

129
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:19,130
He's been eating non-stop for three days straight!

130
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:22,070
Now, then. I'm done eating.

131
00:10:22,770 --> 00:10:23,930
Now I think I'll...

132
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:26,730
pick up some girls!

133
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:36,490
Way to go, kiddo!

134
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:37,700
Can I have your autograph?!

135
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,600
I am Captain Usopp,

136
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,700
the lovable and courageous hero,

137
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,950
who brought down the strongest fishman officer of all!

138
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:44,640
Here's an Usopp anthem!

139
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:50,500
Who was it? Who was it?
Who beat the fishman?

140
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,500
Hmph. How boring.

141
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,470
What is?

142
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,980
I thought you'd be more down in the dumps.

143
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:59,230
Like, "Why didn't this happen before my dad died?!"

144
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,720
That's how I felt at first.

145
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,630
But now I'm thinking about the future.

146
00:11:05,630 --> 00:11:07,390
The future?

147
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:11,230
That straw hat guy and his friends helped us out.

148
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:16,450
But tomorrow, we need to make a fresh start by ourselves.

149
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:19,790
There's no way we can forget the past,

150
00:11:19,790 --> 00:11:21,150
and I don't think we need to.

151
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:25,260
But what's important is what comes next!

152
00:11:25,260 --> 00:11:28,410
What should we do?
What do we need to do?

153
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:32,290
We're the ones who're gonna sustain our villages now.

154
00:11:32,710 --> 00:11:34,590
That's the approach I'm gonna take.

155
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,380
You're so precocious!

156
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:38,710
Oww!

157
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:41,630
Why're you pinching me?!
I don't understand! Why?!

158
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:44,020
And here I was just hoping to tease you again!

159
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:47,890
You've teased me plenty,
you dumb, tattooed punk girl!

160
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:55,230
I'm okay with "punk"!

161
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,650
Will it come off?

162
00:11:59,650 --> 00:12:03,120
I'd like to say, "No problem,"

163
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,730
but there's no way to remove it altogether.

164
00:12:04,730 --> 00:12:09,660
There'll be some scarring.
That's how tattoos are.

165
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:15,630
Yeah. I know it's stupid of me.
They're there for life.

166
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:18,420
I don't want anyone to see this!

167
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:22,090
This... this tattoo...

168
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:26,340
I don't even want to be
in Arlong's crew,

169
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:29,390
but it's like I've been
branded a pirate!

170
00:12:30,430 --> 00:12:31,850
Nami.

171
00:12:34,330 --> 00:12:36,730
Nojiko! What is that?!

172
00:12:36,730 --> 00:12:38,370
Oh? You mean this?

173
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:41,690
It's no big deal!
It's just a decoration!

174
00:12:41,690 --> 00:12:43,570
Now I'm just like you!

175
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:51,850
Say, Doctor.

176
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,970
There's a tattoo I'd like to have.

177
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,380
Here.

178
00:12:58,430 --> 00:13:00,020
Those two can dance!

179
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:03,840
Here's Usopp Anthem No. 185!

180
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:10,560
Bell-mère,

181
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:14,810
your girls have grown up to be positively tough and honorable!

182
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:18,980
They remind me of you.

183
00:13:18,980 --> 00:13:23,440
We're going to live life to its fullest from now on.

184
00:13:24,530 --> 00:13:27,970
We've lost and sacrificed far too much.

185
00:13:27,970 --> 00:13:33,410
Which is why we're gonna smile and laugh like the idiots we are!

186
00:13:35,050 --> 00:13:35,790
Prosciutto and melon!

187
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:41,840
Huh? There's no food around here.
That's no good. Time to go back.

188
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,800
Hold it, boy!

189
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:46,990
A grave? Did someone die?

190
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:49,260
Yeah. A long time ago.

191
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:54,270
Oh, my deepest conveniences.

192
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:59,060
Huh? Deepest concussions.
Huh? Deepest compli–

193
00:13:59,070 --> 00:14:01,580
Deepest condolences.

194
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,930
That's what I meant.

195
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:04,970
Hey, boy.

196
00:14:05,570 --> 00:14:09,400
Nami is going aboard your ship.
She's going to be a pirate.

197
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,050
It'll be a dangerous journey.

198
00:14:11,570 --> 00:14:16,560
If you guys ever do anything to take away her smile,

199
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,960
I will kill you!

200
00:14:18,970 --> 00:14:22,130
Yeah. I'm not gonna do that, though.

201
00:14:22,710 --> 00:14:24,090
Got it?!

202
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:26,510
I got it!

203
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:39,750
This the last of it?

204
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:40,350
Yeah!

205
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:40,770
Alright!

206
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:42,140
Are you finished loading it all?

207
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:43,030
Yeah!

208
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:47,190
Now, then. We got loads of provisions now.
We're good to go.

209
00:14:48,290 --> 00:14:50,280
We were only here a few days,

210
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:52,620
but we made tons of memories
on this island, huh?

211
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:54,030
Yeah!

212
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:04,500
We owe you so much for everything you've done.

213
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,840
We're gonna get back to bounty hunting again!

214
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,970
This is goodbye for now,

215
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:12,430
but we look forward to the day we meet again somewhere!

216
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:14,430
Take care!

217
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:16,620
You guys, too!

218
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:18,890
Well, we should get going, too!

219
00:15:19,970 --> 00:15:22,440
Hey! Hold on!
What about Nami?!

220
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,630
Maybe she's not coming?

221
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:27,070
Why not?!

222
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:31,260
You! You made another pass
at Nami, didn't you?!

223
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:32,520
Why would I do that?

224
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:35,880
Oh, yeah. She achieved her goal,

225
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:34,040
No, you definitely did!

226
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:38,170
and she has no reason to be a pirate,

227
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,780
You can't stand that Nami

228
00:15:35,780 --> 00:15:38,170
and I are all lovey-dovey!

229
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:41,470
so she might be happier here.

230
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:39,160
Are you an idiot?

231
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:40,810
What'd you call me?!

232
00:15:41,470 --> 00:15:43,040
What about my happiness?!

233
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:46,740
If Nami isn't on the ship,

234
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:50,070
then 98.72% of my reason for being here is gone!

235
00:15:50,070 --> 00:15:53,050
By the way, I couldn't find
the prosciutto and melon anywhere!

236
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:54,690
Hey! Where's Nacchan?

237
00:15:54,690 --> 00:15:57,550
That's the thing!
Nobody's seen her since this morning!

238
00:15:57,550 --> 00:16:00,520
What?! She's leaving all the money behind?!

239
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:02,310
The 100 million belly?!

240
00:16:02,310 --> 00:16:05,190
She left it in our house, along with a letter.

241
00:16:05,190 --> 00:16:07,610
She's planning to travel without her money?!

242
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:10,240
But she risked her life to earn it!

243
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,410
She says it's okay,
because she'll just steal some more.

244
00:16:14,770 --> 00:16:17,410
Once that girl says something,
there's no changing her mind.

245
00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:22,790
That fool! We're the ones who still have so much to thank her for!

246
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:30,100
Nami!

247
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:31,400
Nami!

248
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:30,630
Nami!

249
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,590
Nami!

250
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:33,070
Nacchan!

251
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,930
Set sail!

252
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:43,840
Huh? She's started sprinting!

253
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,230
She says to set sail.

254
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:45,690
Wait!

255
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:48,660
Does she really intend to leave

256
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:52,360
without letting us thank her or say goodbye?!

257
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,110
You can't be serious!

258
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:55,070
Hoist the sails!

259
00:16:59,950 --> 00:17:01,380
H-Hey!

260
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:03,130
They're setting sail!

261
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:05,870
Wait! We still haven't thanked you!

262
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,840
Stop, Nacchan!

263
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:10,300
At least let us thank you!

264
00:17:11,210 --> 00:17:12,040
Nacchan!

265
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:16,050
Hold it! I won't let you leave like this!

266
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:19,200
Hey, is this how we should let them say goodbye?

267
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:22,020
Why not? It's her decision.

268
00:17:40,210 --> 00:17:40,780
Nami!

269
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:50,500
Why?!

270
00:17:51,130 --> 00:17:52,250
Nami!

271
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:15,820
She didn't!

272
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:18,570
– What's this...?!
– My wallet's gone!

273
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:20,000
Mine, too!

274
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:20,990
Same here!

275
00:18:26,070 --> 00:18:27,750
Take care, everyone!

276
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:30,100
How dare you!

277
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,540
You damn brat!

278
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:36,700
Hey, she hasn't changed a bit.

279
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,630
Who knows when she'll betray us again.

280
00:18:38,630 --> 00:18:40,310
Nami! Good job!

281
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,740
You lousy pickpocket!

282
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:45,720
Get back here!

283
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,060
Give back our wallets!

284
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:47,890
You punk!

285
00:18:47,890 --> 00:18:49,700
Come back anytime!

286
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:50,730
Take care of yourself!

287
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,560
We're grateful to you guys!

288
00:18:53,930 --> 00:18:55,370
Boy!

289
00:18:56,690 --> 00:18:59,240
Don't forget your promise!

290
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:06,390
Bye, everyone!
I'm heading out!

291
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,420
She got us good!

292
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:14,250
My little sister's gonna do great!

293
00:19:15,650 --> 00:19:16,880
Enjoy yourself!

294
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:23,070
Here, Genzo.

295
00:19:23,070 --> 00:19:25,390
What's this scrap of paper, Doctor?

296
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:30,830
That silly girl. She never learns.
She got another tattoo before she left.

297
00:19:31,690 --> 00:19:33,150
What is this symbol?

298
00:19:33,150 --> 00:19:36,630
It's a tangerine and a pinwheel, apparently.

299
00:19:37,930 --> 00:19:41,210
Oh? Gen!
What happened to your pinwheel?

300
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:47,370
I doubt there's any need for it now.

301
00:19:59,030 --> 00:20:00,290
I'm heading out!

302
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:10,270
Hold on, Gen-san!
Stay away from Nami!

303
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:14,210
No, but, I want to see her smile, too!

304
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:17,590
She starts crying because you have such a scary face!

305
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:20,030
But what am I supposed to do about that?

306
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:21,240
I know!

307
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:25,050
This'll make you laugh, right?!
If I always keep it here like this?!

308
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:27,200
What do you say, Nami-chan?

309
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:30,790
Look. I really don't think a dumb pinwheel is going to make Nami...

310
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:40,710
Oh. She laughed.
